Third-party libraries vendored into cardano-c
=============================================

Each dependency below is vendored under lib/external/<name>/, compiled as an
isolated CMake OBJECT library with warnings and clang-tidy disabled for that
target only, and folded into libcardano-c. The upstream license text is kept
verbatim in each directory; copyright notices are never altered. All listed
licenses are compatible with the project's Apache-2.0 license.

libsodium
  Use:      SHA-256, SHA-512, Blake2b, Ed25519, HMAC, constant-time compare.
  License:  ISC (see libsodium/LICENSE).
  Origin:   https://github.com/jedisct1/libsodium

gmp (mini-gmp)
  Use:      arbitrary-precision integers backing cardano_bigint_t.
  License:  LGPL/GPL dual (see gmp/README and the headers).
  Origin:   https://gmplib.org (mini-gmp subset)

sha3
  Use:      SHA3-256 and Keccak-256 (shared Keccak-f permutation, differing
            domain pad byte).
  Version:  tiny_sha3 @ dcbb3192047c2a721f5f851db591871d428036a9
  License:  MIT (see sha3/LICENSE).
  Origin:   https://github.com/mjosaarinen/tiny_sha3
  Details:  sha3/VERSION.txt

ripemd160
  Use:      RIPEMD-160 (20-byte digest).
  Version:  trezor-firmware crypto/ripemd160.c @
            fb471a96f226737ec1c22bbf88078f5b36a572bc
            (Litzenberger 2008, public-domain changes by Wuille 2012)
  License:  Public domain (see ripemd160/LICENSE).
  Origin:   https://github.com/trezor/trezor-firmware
  Details:  ripemd160/VERSION.txt

secp256k1
  Use:      secp256k1 ECDSA-verify and Schnorr (BIP340) verify backing the
            verifyEcdsaSecp256k1Signature and verifySchnorrSecp256k1Signature
            builtins. Only the verify path plus the extrakeys and schnorrsig
            modules are compiled; recovery, ECDH, ellswift and musig are
            dropped.
  Version:  bitcoin-core/secp256k1 v0.6.0 @
            0cdc758a56360bf58a851fe91085a327ec97685a
  License:  MIT (see secp256k1/COPYING).
  Origin:   https://github.com/bitcoin-core/secp256k1
  Details:  secp256k1/VERSION.txt
  Build:    No autotools and no codegen. Configured by compile defines on the
            OBJECT target (ENABLE_MODULE_EXTRAKEYS, ENABLE_MODULE_SCHNORRSIG,
            ECMULT_WINDOW_SIZE=8, SECP256K1_STATIC); the checked-in precomputed
            tables are compiled as-is. The small window keeps the verify table
            at 8 KiB instead of 1 MiB, since secp verify is a cold path.

blst
  Use:      BLS12-381 G1/G2 arithmetic, pairings, hash-to-curve and
            serialization backing the bls12_381_* Plutus builtins.
  Version:  supranational/blst v0.3.14 @
            8c7db7fe8d2ce6e76dc398ebd4d475c0ec564355
  License:  Apache-2.0 (see blst/LICENSE).
  Origin:   https://github.com/supranational/blst
  Details:  blst/VERSION.txt
  Build:    Portable no-assembly build. Only src/server.c is a compilation
            unit; it includes the implementation .c files it needs. The
            OBJECT target sets __BLST_NO_ASM__ (reference C field arithmetic
            in no_asm.h) and __BLST_PORTABLE__ (pure-C SHA-256, no runtime
            asm dispatch), so there is no assembly and the target builds on
            WASM and the armv6/armv7 cross builds. src/vect.h was reordered so
            the no-asm 32-bit-limb path is also taken on x86_64/aarch64; no
            copyright text was altered. The asm/ and build/ trees, the C++ and
            language bindings, and the alternative client_min_* amalgamation
            units are dropped.
